Bentley: BSIVer audit version section (replaces BentleyVersionString.c).

Mike's audit tool locates the underlying OpenSSL version by finding the "BSIVer" PE
section with DumpBin (it is matched by section name, not by an exported symbol). This is
Windows-only (_MSC_VER) and is appended to cversion.c because that translation unit is
always compiled and always linked (OpenSSL_version* are pulled in by normal usage).

The version string is derived from OPENSSL_VERSION_STR (already in scope in this file), so
it tracks the vcpkg-pinned OpenSSL version automatically. As in the original
BentleyVersionString.c, the array is `static`: the audit tool matches it by the "BSIVer"
section name, not by an exported symbol, so no .def entry is needed, and because OpenSSL is
not built with /Gw the named-section data is not COMDAT and /OPT:REF cannot strip it (this
matches the long-shipping original, which carried no /INCLUDE and survived). If a future
toolset enables /Gw and the audit tool can no longer find the section, force it in with
`#pragma comment(linker, "/INCLUDE:...")` (note: requires non-static and the correct
name decoration per architecture) or export it via the .def.

--- a/crypto/cversion.c
+++ b/crypto/cversion.c
@@ -137,3 +137,12 @@ const char *OpenSSL_version(int t)
     }
     return "not available";
 }
+
+/* Bentley: BSIVer audit section. Windows-only; matched by section name via DumpBin. */
+#ifdef _MSC_VER
+# pragma const_seg("BSIVer")
+# pragma const_seg()
+static __declspec(allocate("BSIVer")) char szSourceFileVersionString[] =
+    "#@!~BeOpenSSL " OPENSSL_VERSION_STR "; OpenSSL " OPENSSL_VERSION_STR ", "
+    OPENSSL_VERSION_STR "~!@#";
+#endif
